cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about attribute guided face image synthesis, which involves generating realistic face images with specific attributes. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), as it requires the use of deep learning models to learn how to generate images. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic data augmentation, which is a common technique in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant to the paper's content.
